  <description><![CDATA[<p>With views towards the ocean, a great location, friendly staff and a number of facilities to go with it the Hotel Melia Madeira Mare can be enjoyed by all.</p>
<h2>Your holiday of relaxation</h2>
<p>There’s nothing that puts you in the holiday mood quite like a swim in the outdoor pool and this one offers marvellous views towards the ocean. The 260m² pool cools you off on hot summer days and with plenty of sun-loungers surrounding it there’s no greater place to unwind. The spa also offers total relaxation with a hamman, whirlpool and chromotherapy shower as well as massages and treatments available (all spa facilities and treatments are payable locally). The La Luna bar is great for those who love live music, you can listen whilst treating yourself to a delicious cocktail.</p>
<h2>Located in the Lido area</h2>
<p>Positioned in the Lido area of São Martinho, just 3 kilometres from Funchal you have the best of both worlds with the sea a few minutes walk away or hop on a bus and head to the hustle and bustle of the city centre. Buses run regularly to the centre of Funchal and you can catch one just outside the hotel, walking is always an option too - just be prepared for the hills! The lido area is also fun to explore, it’s popular with tourists and there are a number of restaurants and bars in the area to try out. For those wanting to dip their toes in the cool, blue waters of the ocean then you’re just a short walk away.</p>
<h2>Ocean inspired decor</h2>
<p>The hotels decor is inspired by its ocean front location with cool, contemporary colours with stylised design. Rooms are generous in size and all offer a balcony, great for being able to enjoy some peace and maybe dive into a great book.</p>]]></description>
