  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Twin Side Ocean View Rooms</strong> sleep up to three people and have a bath.</p>
<p><strong>Twin Ocean View rooms</strong> sleep up to three people, have a bathtub and have beautiful views out towards the sea. </p>
<p><strong>Superior Ocean View rooms</strong> sleep up to three people, have a bathtub with showerhead attachment and also enjoy beautiful sea views. There is a small kitchenette and lounge area.</p>
<p><strong>Master Suites</strong> sleep up to three people (extra bed is a sofa bed), have a bathtub and shower as well as an impressive 32m² balcony/terrace where you can enjoy fantastic sea views.</p>
<p><strong>Premium Suites</strong> sleep up to three people (extra bed is a sofa bed), have a small lounge area as well as a kitchenette. They're approx. 44m².</p>
<p><strong>Twin Side Ocean View</strong> and <strong>Ocean View Rooms</strong> are available for <strong>sole use</strong>. These rooms are on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Bedroom facilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Balcony</li>
<li>Tea &amp; coffee making facilities</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Bathrobe &amp; slippers</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>From the 1st of June 2024 a tourist tax of approx. €2.00 per person per night, for a maximum of 7 nights is payable locally for guests age 13 years and over (subject to change).</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>]]></roomsDescription>
